<module>
    <h>falt</h>
    <p><g>falt</g>
        <en>hair</en> is a masculine <a href="?xx=nouns/simple_common_nouns">simple common
        noun</a>.</p>

    <section id="forms">
        <h>forms</h>
        <p>The principal parts of <g>falt</g> are – <ul>
                <li><m>falt</m> – nominative/dative singular, genitive plural</li>
                <li><m>fuilt</m> – genitive singular, nominative/dative plural</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <section id="definiteness">
            <h>definiteness</h>
            <p><ul>
                    <li>indefinite <ul>
                            <li>singular <ul>
                                    <li>nominative – <m>falt</m></li>
                                    <li>dative – le <m>falt</m></li>
                                    <li>genitive – dath <m>fuilt</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                            <li>plural <ul>
                                    <li>nominative – <m>fuilt</m></li>
                                    <li>dative – le <m>fuilt</m></li>
                                    <li>genitive – dathan <m>fhalt</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                        </ul></li>
                    <li>definite <ul>
                            <li>singular <ul>
                                    <li>nominative – <m>am falt</m></li>
                                    <li>dative – leis <m>an fhalt</m></li>
                                    <li>genitive – dath <m>an fhuilt</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                            <li>plural <ul>
                                    <li>nominative – <m>na fuilt</m></li>
                                    <li>dative – leis <m>na fuilt</m></li>
                                    <li>genitive – dathan <m>nam falt</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                        </ul></li>
                </ul></p>
        </section>
        <section id="number">
            <h>number</h>
            <p><ul>
                    <li>singular <ul>
                            <li>indefinite <ul>
                                    <li>nominative – <m>falt</m></li>
                                    <li>dative – le <m>falt</m></li>
                                    <li>genitive – dath <m>fuilt</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                            <li>definite <ul>
                                    <li>nominative – <m>am falt</m></li>
                                    <li>dative – leis <m>an fhalt</m></li>
                                    <li>genitive – earball <m>a’ chait</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                        </ul></li>
                    <li>plural <ul>
                            <li>indefinite <ul>
                                    <li>nominative – <m>fuilt</m></li>
                                    <li>dative – le <m>fuilt</m></li>
                                    <li>genitive – dathan <m>fhalt</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                            <li>definite <ul>
                                    <li>nominative – <m>na fuilt</m></li>
                                    <li>dative – leis <m>na fuilt</m></li>
                                    <li>genitive – dathan <m>nam falt</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                        </ul></li>
                </ul></p>
        </section>
        <section id="case">
            <h>case</h>
            <p><ul>
                    <li>nominative <ul>
                            <li>indefinite <ul>
                                    <li>singular – <m>falt</m></li>
                                    <li>plural – <m>fuilt</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                            <li>definite <ul>
                                    <li>singular – <m>am falt</m></li>
                                    <li>plural – <m>na fuilt</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                        </ul></li>
                    <li>dative <ul>
                            <li>indefinite <ul>
                                    <li>singular – le <m>falt</m></li>
                                    <li>plural – le <m>fuilt</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                            <li>definite <ul>
                                    <li>singular – leis <m>an fhalt</m></li>
                                    <li>plural – leis <m>na fuilt</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                        </ul></li>
                    <li>genitive <ul>
                            <li>indefinite <ul>
                                    <li>singular – dath <m>fuilt</m></li>
                                    <li>plural – dathan <m>fhalt</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                            <li>definite <ul>
                                    <li>singular – dath <m>an fhuilt</m></li>
                                    <li>plural – dathan <m>nam falt</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                        </ul></li>
                </ul></p>
        </section>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>dependents</h>
        <section id="deps-mods">
            <h>modifiers</h>
            <p><g>falt</g> can take an attributive <a href="?xx=adjectives/adjectives">adjective</a> modifier.</p>
            <p>Some examples – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha <m>falt dubh</m> air Calum ach tha <m>falt bàn</m> air Màiri.</gd>
                        <tr>Calum has black hair but Mary has fair hair.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 9</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>uses</h>
        <section id="uses-sbj">
            <h>subject</h>
            <p><g>falt</g> can act as the subject of a <a href="?xx=verbs/verbs">verb</a>.</p>
            <p>Some examples with <a href="?gd=bi"><g>bi</g></a>
                <en>be</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha <m>falt</m> dubh air Calum ach tha <m>falt</m> bàn air Màiri.</gd>
                        <tr>Calum has black hair but Mary has fair hair.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 9</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>


</module>
